there had to be people who would be interested in these slightly unhinged but oh so enjoyable vehicles.’[/vc_column_text][vc_single_image image=\"137\" img_size=\"full\" el_class=\"unique_approchimg\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"font_roboto\"]Drastically modifying the Defender and restoring the parts that remain stock sounds like a form of restomodding, but we at Tophat are rather skeptical about this mostly overrated term. There are plenty examples of Land Rovers around that have not been restored properly and modified in a downright unsafe manner. That is exactly what Tophat tries to avoid at all cost and that is why we put so much effort in developing completely new suspension and brakes.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner el_class=\"plr-50 about_col font_roboto\" width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"font_roboto\"]The love for the Defander’s basic design is an important factor for us, but this doesn’t mean we love every single detail about it. Many quirks and peculiarities become minor or even major annoyances overtime and we don’t want our customers to only experience love at first sight when they see our vehicles; we want them to develop a lasting affection. By using our creativity, we managed to develop a basic concept – a starting point if you will – that is already quite out of the ordinary. Every Tophat Defender comes standard with an LS3, LT1 or LT4 V8 engine, ranging from just over 400 to almost 700 horsepower, or more if clients so desire. The standard suspension of a Defender is not known for its comfort, precision and roadholding, so to keep the driving experience both enjoyable and safe, every Tophat Defender comes standard with a custom designed air suspension system including Koni shock absorbers, large AP Racing brakes and enforced internals from the gearbox through the transfer case and differentials to the drive shafts.[/vc_column_text][vc_single_image image=\"139\" img_size=\"full\" el_class=\"unique_approchimg\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"font_roboto\"]With our in-house designers constantly working on new ideas to improve our products, hands-on experience from out technicians who build the cars and close relationships with our customers, valuable feedback is used to implement new ideas and developments to further enhance our vehicles. Make sure to follow us or allow us to keep you up to date about our latest developments.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row el_class=\"home_bg_sec\" css=\".vc_custom_1659199385667{background-image: url(http://localhost/projects/tophatclassics/wp-content/uploads/2022/07/im_banner_logo-1.png?id=143) !important;}\"][vc_column][/vc_column][/vc_row]', 'Media', '', 'inherit', 'closed', 'closed', '', '33-revision-v1', '', '', '2022-07-30 17:21:19', '2022-07-30 17:21:19', '', 33, 'http://localhost/projects/tophatclassics/?p=157', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
